<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-223-040  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 223 040.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Feb 27 1990 n1373* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>British Telecom gives orders to BICC, GEC Plessey for multi-mediafibre trial. (BICC Cables)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   British Telecommunications PLC (contracts)GEC Plessey Telecommunications (contracts)Fulcrum Communications Ltd. (contracts)BICC Cables (contracts).andO;Topic:     ContractsMultimedia TechnologyFiber OpticsTelephone SystemsTelevision Networks.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>BRITISH TELECOM GIVES ORDERS TO BICC, GECandM;PLESSEY FOR MULTI-MEDIA FIBRE TRIALandM;British Telecommunications Plc has placed contracts worth #4.5m with threesuppliers for the equipment required in its trial optical fibre network atBishop's Stortford, Hertfordshire, which is to provide voice andentertainment services to 400 residential and business customers there (CI No1,166).andP;  GEC Plessey Telecommunications is to supply the TPON - telephony onpassive optical networks - equipment for television, home shopping anddatabase access; wholly-owned British Telecom subsidiary FulcrumCommunications Ltd is to supply the broadband integrated distributed starsystem, which unlike TPON is an active network using electronic switches withwhich a customer can select TV and radio programmes and telephone services;and BICC Cables will supply the optical fibre cables and ancillary equipmentrequired for both of the two systems.andP;  Delivery has already started and thetrial, which is designed to show whether this technology is feasible or not,should start this autumn.andO;</TEXT></DOC>